Typical Memory Representation Of a C program consist of following section - 
1)Text segment
2)Initialized data segment
3)uninitialized data segment
4)Heap
5)Stack



Text Segment / Code segment
It contain executable instructions
It is below heap segment

Initialized data segment - 
Contain global and static variables that are initialized by programmer

Uninitialized data segment - /Block started by symbol

Stack 
It stores automatic variables and at the time of  every function call new stack gets created.

Heap  
Heap is a section where dynamic memory allocation takes place.


